        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:58PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northwestern Colorado Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Air Force Academy, Manitou Springs, Black Forest,
Falcon, Cimarron Hills, and Peterson Space Force Base.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
